 You have to know God feels unfair at times

262
00:11:37,340 --> 00:11:41,200
 when we focus too much on what we deserve

263
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,240
 and too little on what God deserves.

264
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:48,720
 God will feel unfair when you focus too much

265
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:52,040
 on what you deserve and too little on what he deserves.

266
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:53,160
 We can tell that this is the case

267
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:56,280
 just by way of looking at their offerings

268
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,740
 in contrast to one another.

269
00:11:57,740 --> 00:12:01,660
 You see, Cain, he brings what the text says

270
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:03,380
 is an offering of the fruit of the ground,

271
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:05,160
 which is a legitimate offering.

272
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:07,120
 He brings what Leviticus 2 tells us

273
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,720
 is a cereal or a grain offering.

274
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,960
 And yet what's really unique about grain offerings

275
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,840
 is they're unlike any other offering in Leviticus.

276
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:18,360
 We know that they're not bound by strict rigid,

277
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,440
 they're not bound by rigidity or rules.

278
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,600
 There's some flexibility

279
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,840
 in how you can actually express this offering

280
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:26,320
 because it was considered a free will offering.

281
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:29,800
 The thought there being that you could offer to God

282
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:33,760
 what you wanted, however much you wanted,

283
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,720
 which should beg a question in our mind.

284
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,560
 Okay, well then how much

285
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:41,000
 did Cain actually want to give to God?

286
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:46,960
 He gives an indistinct bundle of produce.

287
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:50,680
 It's legitimate, but it's not very detailed.

288
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:52,360
 Whereas in contrast, we look at Abel

289
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:54,440
 who brought the firstborn of his flock

290
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,600
 and their fat portions.

291
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,840
 Do you see the difference?

292
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,980
 There's just more detail.

293
00:12:57,980 --> 00:13:00,840
 He gives the firstborn of his flock.

294
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:03,840
 Like he gives the strength of those little lambies

295
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,920
 that he raised up, the very first one,

296
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:08,100
 that one which would have been useful for resourcing,

297
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:10,440
 for wool and for mating and eventually for food.

298
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,960
 He takes it and he offers it to God.

299
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,000
 And he gives to God the fat portions,

300
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,960
 like that most nourishing and precious part of the animal.

301
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,440
 He offers it to God.

302
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,280
 He doesn't show it to God

303
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:22,320
 and offer him a USDA select sirloin.

304
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,240
 He says, "Hey, you know what?

305
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,200
 "I've got the Wagyu rib eye, here you go, God."

306
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:28,340
 He offers him the very best thing that he can

307
00:13:28,340 --> 00:13:29,920
 because God likes that cut.

308
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:34,080
 And what we see is that God has favor for Abel

309
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,260
 by way of what he offers.

310
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,720
 I love the way that Richard Hess says it.

311
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,200
 He says, "By giving the firstborn

312
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,760
 "and the best of the animal, the fat,

313
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:46,760
 "Abel would be understood as having given everything to God."

314
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,240
 Do you see it?

315
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:51,520
 Cain gives something to God

316
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:55,640
 while Abel gives everything to God.

317
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:59,760
 And here's the lesson that you need to know.

318
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:05,160
 You can tell a lot about the offerer

319
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:08,960
 by way of their offering.

320
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:12,920
 You can tell a lot about the offerer

321
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,840
 by way of their offering.

322
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:18,360
 I learned this lesson very plainly just two weeks ago

323
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:20,800
 when I and every other husband in DFW

324
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,560
 arose at the crack of dawn and visited a local grocery store

325
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,640
 because it was Valentine's Day

326
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,200
 and we needed to buy our wives flowers.

327
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,380
 It's quite the sight.

328
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:29,960
 It's just a bunch of men

329
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,920
 walking around the floral department

330
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:36,440
 trying to pick out whatever they think their wife might like.

331
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,720
 And as I'm there, I run into a guy

332
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,360
 that goes to church here at Watermark.

333
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,040
 And so we strike up conversation and ask him,

334
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:43,320
 "Hey man, what's the plan for the day?"

335
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,720
 And he looks at me with all of his kids in tow

336
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,560
 and he says, "Well, we've already sent mama

337
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,060
 "for a little bit of a spa day.

338
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:50,140
 "Give her a little bit of me time.

339
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,920
 "And me and the kids, we're getting her some flowers

340
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:55,640
 "and we're gonna go make some homemade Valentine's cards."

341
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:58,040
 And as he said this to me, I thought to myself,

342
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:02,440
 that's a man that knows what his woman loves

343
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:07,440
 because the offering says a lot about the offerer.

344
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:11,100
 So let me ask you this, what are you offering to God?

345
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:13,780
 What are you offering to him?

346
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:17,040
 Would you offer him the day?

347
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,140
 Would you offer him this week?

348
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:21,040
 What did you offer him with respect to your time?

349
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,520
 Like, did you give him your time

350
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,680
 just whenever it was convenient

351
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:27,600
 or did you give him your time whenever it wasn't convenient?

352
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,120
 When it came to the scripture,

353
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,200
 did you take the easy route

354
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,960
 and let someone else explain to you

355
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,560
 whatever it is that God might've said

356
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,440
 or did you go the hard route,

357
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,800
 study them on your own,

358
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,680
 meditate even when it was difficult

359
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:43,200
 because you don't want to hear what someone has to say.

360
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,160
 God might've said,

361
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:46,960
 you want to hear what he has to say himself.

362
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:50,680
 What about prayer?

363
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:53,920
 Did you treat prayer like it's just the last resort?

364
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:57,580
 Or did you treat prayer like it was the first response

365
00:15:57,580 --> 00:15:59,640
 whenever that thing happened this week,

366
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:02,160
 that problem popped up out of nowhere,

367
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:04,680
 whenever trouble seemed to arise

368
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:06,520
 and you did not know what to do,

369
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:09,340
 did you pray as your first response?

370
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:13,160
 Do you walk into rooms like this,

371
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:16,600
 indifferent about the thought of meeting with God?

372
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,760
 Or do you walk into rooms like this,

373
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:23,660
 expectant that God wants to meet with you?

374
00:16:23,660 --> 00:16:26,920
 Do you worship?

375
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:29,560
 This might be too personal.

376
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:34,160
 Do you worship in a way where all of your attention

377
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,840
 is just about you?

378
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,080
 I don't want to stand out.

379
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,480
 I don't want to sound weird.

380
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,860
 I don't want to look bad.

381
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:41,440
 Or do you worship in a way

382
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,640
 where all of your attention is about him?

383
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:46,700
 What are you offering to God?

384
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:49,480
 How much are you offering to God?

385
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:52,240
 Abel, Abel brings the first fruit.

386
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:54,420
 He brings the very best of what he has to give.

387
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:56,360
 He gives the fat portion to God

388
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:59,160
 because he knows God is worth everything.

389
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,120
 And we have to know the same thing.

390
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,520
 You see, here's the problem.

391
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:05,320
 Often we accuse God of not being fair to us

392
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:07,520
 when we are guilty of not being fair to him.

393
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,880
 You tracking with that?

394
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,520
 Like we often look at God and we're like,

395
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,120
 where are you at God?

396
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:14,700
 You're not being fair to me.

397
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,200
 And yet the reality is, if we look at our time,

398
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,360
 we examine our calendar,

399
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:20,000
 we pay attention to our transactions,

400
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,360
 we would realize we're the ones that's not being fair to him.

401
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:25,520
 We would offer him something

402
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:27,760
 when he actually deserves everything.

403
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,480
 That's what we see all throughout the scripture.

404
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,680
 Revelation 4, 11 says,

405
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:34,480
 "Worthy are you, O Lord and God,

406
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:37,000
 to receive glory and honor and power,

407
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,960
 for you created all things,

408
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:44,000
 and by your will they existed and were created."

409
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:44,920
 Do you hear it?

410
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,960
 First Timothy 1, 17,

411
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:51,960
 "Now to the King, eternal, immortal, invisible,

412
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:57,480
 the only God, be honor and glory forever and ever, amen."

413
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,240
 Romans 11, 36,

414
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:05,240
 "For from him and through him and to him

415
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:08,000
 are all things.

416
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:13,000
 To him and him alone be glory forever and ever, amen."

417
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,900
 Are you tracking with what this is saying?

418
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:19,320
 So why then, Christian,

419
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,000
 if you are a member of the family of God,

420
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,360
 if you identify as a follower of Jesus,

421
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,120
 if you believe these things are true,

422
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:29,200
 why is it that you're living with a calculated devotion?

423
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:33,680
 Will you give to God some part of yourself,

424
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,960
 maybe even most of yourself,

425
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,440
 but you don't give to God every part of yourself.

426
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,680
 You think Christ went to the cross

427
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,360
 just to die for some part of you?

428
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:45,160
 No, Christ went to the cross to die for every part of you.

429
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,240
 And the reason we know that

430
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,360
 is because he didn't just give up some part of himself,

431
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:51,480
 he gave up all of himself.

432
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:52,440
 If that's the case,

433
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:55,880
 if he would willingly offer all of himself to you,

434
00:18:55,880 --> 00:19:00,880
 why then can we not offer all of ourself to him in return?

435
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,400
 This is the issue.

436
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:07,400
 We think God is unfair when we in fact are unfair,

437
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,560
 because the fairest thing we could do

438
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:13,160
 is give him everything we've got.

439
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,640
 That's your first point.

440
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,300
 Second, we find in verse four,

441
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:21,240
 "And the Lord had regard for Abel in his offering,

442
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:25,040
 but for Cain in his offering, he had no regard.

443
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:27,960
 So Cain was very angry and his face fell.

444
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:30,600
 The Lord said to Cain, 'Why are you angry?

445
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,820
 Why is your face fallen?

446
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:35,680
 If you do well, will you not be accepted?

447
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,340
 And if you do not do well,

448
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:40,220
 sin is crouching at the door, its desires for you,

449
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:42,520
 and you must rule over it.'"

450
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:48,440
 So both Cain and Abel, they bring offerings to God, yes?

451
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,040
 And yet what we just saw

452
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:54,600
 is that God only regards Abel's offering.

453
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,280
 It's kind of a weird word, right?

454
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,240
 God regarded.

455
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,360
 Well, if you look in the Hebrew,

456
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:00,280
 the idea behind that word regarded

457
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:04,480
 is he looked or he gazed upon, not just the offering,

458
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:09,080
 he actually gazes upon Abel and Abel's offering,

459
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:14,080
 which feels unfair, because again, Cain, firstborn,

460
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:16,620
 and so his responsibility

461
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:19,080
 as one of the representative heads of the family

462
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:23,800
 is to present offerings to God as his father would.

463
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:26,900
 And yet here's Abel doing the same thing.

464
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:30,280
 And it's Abel that God seems to regard.

465
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:33,040
 He's the one that he looks at, but Cain isn't.

466
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:34,640
 That feels so unfair of God,

467
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,480
 and yet we have to ask the question,

468
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:39,100
 then was there something wrong with Cain's offering?

469
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,440
 No.

470
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:43,680
 Again, Cain's offering is totally suitable.

471
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,680
 It's a cereal offering.

472
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,780
 It's a grain offering.

473
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:48,380
 It's perfectly legit to give to God.

474
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:49,920
 It doesn't mean that there was something wrong

475
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,400
 with Cain's offering, but catch this,

476
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:54,240
 it does mean that there was something right

477
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,400
 about Abel's offering.

478
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:58,560
 So several years ago, Brooke and I,

479
00:20:58,560 --> 00:20:59,640
 we were in Florence, Italy,

480
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:03,120
 and we were walking through the Academia Gallery.

481
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,280
 If you're familiar with the Academia,

482
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,840
 then what you know is most people go to the Academia

483
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:09,640
 not to see all of the marble sculptures

484
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,800
 that they have littered across their premises,

485
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,980
 and they are incredible sculptures within their own right,

486
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:16,120
 but people don't go there

487
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:18,380
 for all the myriad of other sculptures.

488
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:20,720
 They go there for one sculpture and one sculpture alone.

489
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:23,480
 They go there for Michelangelo's David,

490
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:26,240
 and it's not because the other sculptures are bad.

491
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,800
 The other sculptures are good,

492
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:32,280
 but David is better.

493
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:38,020
 You see, David is greater than the rest

494
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:42,080
 because though they are good, he is great,

495
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:44,040
 and that's what's happening here.

496
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:48,400
 You see, Cain has not been rejected by God in this moment.

497
00:21:50,060 --> 00:21:54,220
 Abel is merely being favored by God in this moment,

498
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:58,960
 and yet in this moment,

499
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:02,840
 Cain experiences the entirety of what's happening

500
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:05,920
 as personal rejection.

501
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:10,680
 That's why comparison is so very,

502
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,460
 that's why comparison is so very costly

503
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:15,140
 because Cain doesn't realize what we need to realize,

504
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:17,600
 that favor for somebody else

505
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:20,000
 does not mean disfavor for you.

506
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:26,320
 Favor for somebody else does not mean disfavor for you.

507
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:28,220
 That was Cain's experience.

508
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:31,400
 It says that he grew angry and his face dropped.

509
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,240
 I love that.

510
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,880
 Like you can just picture what's happening to him.

511
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,160
 That idea of he grew angry

512
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:37,860
 is the thought of him getting heated anger,

513
00:22:37,860 --> 00:22:39,200
 like his blood starts to boil,

514
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,040
 he gets hot is what happens,

515
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:43,040
 and then it says that his face drops,

516
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:45,840
 like his face falls,

517
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,920
 and yet what's happening is you see those two images,

518
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:50,480
 like a little kid who crosses his arms and ducks his head

519
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:52,400
 and starts muttering under his breath.

520
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:55,040
 What we realize is two things are true of him in this moment.

521
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:59,240
 He is both vindictive and he is victimized,

522
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:01,000
 which is a really potent mix

523
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,080
 because what it tells us is he feels

524
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:05,320
 like he didn't get what he deserved,

525
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:09,240
 and he's willing to do something about it.

526
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:12,240
 He's willing to take action to honor the injustice

527
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:14,320
 he feels like he has suffered.

528
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,760
 That's what makes comparison so dangerous

529
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:21,320
 because often we internalize somebody else's success

530
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:23,440
 as our own personal failure,

531
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:26,600
 and yet that's just not true.

532
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,000
 Like just because somebody gets promoted

533
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:30,320
 doesn't mean that your boss hates you.

534
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:32,160
 Just because you have a friend who starts dating somebody

535
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,040
 doesn't mean that nobody wants you.

536
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:37,460
 Just because you see somebody succeed

537
00:23:37,460 --> 00:23:39,520
 doesn't mean that they're a threat to you.

538
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:41,280
 Just because you're scrolling through Instagram

539
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,280
 a little bit too long

540
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:44,160
 and you realize that everybody's moving ahead

541
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,320
 doesn't mean that you're left behind.

542
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:49,080
 What we do is we, in the process of comparing,

543
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:53,160
 we often find ourselves growing in resentment.

544
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,560
 What's resentment?

545
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,180
 Resentment is not just wanting what other people have,

546
00:23:57,180 --> 00:23:58,960
 it's hating them for having it.

547
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:03,540
 And yet comparison often breeds this type of response.

548
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:05,240
 That's what the author of Hebrews writes.

549
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,880
 He writes in Hebrews chapter 12,

550
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,160
 "Strive for peace with everyone

551
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:10,240
 "and for the holiness without which

552
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,480
 "no one will see the Lord.

553
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:15,560
 "See to it that no one fails to obtain the grace of God,

554
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:21,420
 "that no root of bitterness springs up and causes trouble,

555
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:24,840
 "and by it many become defiled."

556
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:27,280
 What's the author saying?

557
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:33,660
 He's saying that our issue is not the fruit of resentment.

558
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:38,600
 What they have, how much they have,

559
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:40,700
 what they achieve, what you can't seem to.

560
00:24:41,500 --> 00:24:43,020
 Our issue is not the fruit of resentment,

561
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:45,840
 it's the root of resentment.

562
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:48,620
 And when we evaluate the root of resentment,

563
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:49,940
 what we need to know is that our issue

564
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:52,420
 is not with anybody else.

565
00:24:52,420 --> 00:24:54,360
 Our issue is with God.

566
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:57,780
 That's the truth of it.

567
00:24:57,780 --> 00:25:01,260
 If you find yourself boiling and brooding

568
00:25:01,260 --> 00:25:04,060
 because they've got something that you think you deserve,

569
00:25:04,060 --> 00:25:07,560
 your issue is not with them.

570
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:10,260
 Your issue is with Him.

571
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:13,660
 You see, that's what we realize

572
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:16,060
 as we study through this thing.

573
00:25:16,060 --> 00:25:18,820
 We realize that Cain feels like many of us do.

574
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:20,380
 He feels cheated, he feels mistreated,

575
00:25:20,380 --> 00:25:21,900
 he feels underappreciated.

576
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:23,260
 Anybody ever felt like that?

577
00:25:23,260 --> 00:25:25,620
 Here's the crazy thing about it.

578
00:25:25,620 --> 00:25:29,540
 God is actually the only one that has been cheated.

579
00:25:29,540 --> 00:25:32,140
 He is the only one that has been mistreated.

580
00:25:32,140 --> 00:25:35,620
 He is the only one that has been underappreciated

581
00:25:35,620 --> 00:25:40,040
 because He is the only one worthy of anything.

582
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,720
 That's the great irony here.

583
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:44,180
 We feel disfavored by God

584
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:49,500
 when God has been disfavored by us.

585
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:52,220
 That's what Romans 3 tells us in verses 11 and 12.

586
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:55,860
 It says, "None is righteous, no, not one.

587
00:25:55,860 --> 00:25:58,300
 "No one understands, no one seeks for God.

588
00:25:58,300 --> 00:25:59,660
 "All have turned aside together.

589
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:01,100
 "They have become worthless.

590
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:03,860
 "No one does good, not even one."

591
00:26:05,580 --> 00:26:10,420
 Don't you see, like, we turn our backs on God.

592
00:26:10,420 --> 00:26:13,180
 We turned our back on God

593
00:26:13,180 --> 00:26:15,260
 before the thought ever even crossed our mind

594
00:26:15,260 --> 00:26:17,460
 that He might've turned His back on us.

595
00:26:17,460 --> 00:26:22,420
 So how does He respond to us when we do that to Him?

596
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:24,740
 Does He smite us where we stand?

597
00:26:24,740 --> 00:26:27,200
 Does He render judgment from afar?

598
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:29,900
 Does He condemn you to hell with no hope at all?

599
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:32,240
 No.

600
00:26:34,540 --> 00:26:38,060
 I love it, His response in this story

601
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,620
 is the same response that He had in the last story.

602
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:44,380
 He just starts asking questions.

603
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:46,420
 And the fascinating thing is,

604
00:26:46,420 --> 00:26:47,700
 He just starts asking questions

605
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:49,560
 that He already knows the answers to,

606
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:54,240
 but we ourselves have not yet answered.

607
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:56,620
 So what are the questions?

608
00:26:56,620 --> 00:27:00,040
 He looks at Cain.

609
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:03,180
 And friend, I think He's looking at you.

610
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:05,780
 And He's asking you, "Why are you angry?

611
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:08,700
 "Why are you angry?"

612
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:10,420
 Like, is it because you didn't get

613
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:11,940
 what you thought you deserved?

614
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:17,780
 Is it because someone achieved that thing that you wanted?

615
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:20,100
 Is it because you feel like life's been unfair?

616
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:22,700
 Maybe it's not, "Why are you angry?"

617
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,220
 Maybe it's, "Why is your face fallen?

618
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,620
 "Why are you so downcast?

619
00:27:27,620 --> 00:27:29,140
 "Do you fear that you'll never be happy?

620
00:27:29,140 --> 00:27:31,100
 "Do you fear that I've forgotten you?

621
00:27:31,100 --> 00:27:32,900
 "Do you fear that I've forgotten you?

622
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:34,460
 "Do you fear that I don't hear your prayers

623
00:27:34,460 --> 00:27:35,360
 "when they rise up to heaven?

624
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:38,820
 "Do you fear that this is all that will ever be for you?"

625
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:42,520
 The amazing thing about this story

626
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:45,220
 is it communicates to us the character and nature of God,

627
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:49,980
 is we learn that God comes to us

628
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:53,140
 the same way He came to Cain.

629
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:56,680
 He comes reaching out, wanting to process

630
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,260
 and talk through it all.

631
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:00,980
 He comes asking questions

632
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:03,220
 and ultimately affirming for us

633
00:28:03,220 --> 00:28:07,060
 that there is still favor for you too.

634
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:10,780
 This is the thing that wrecked me

635
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:13,700
 because it is so easy in our modern age

636
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,900
 to look left and right and see what everybody else has

637
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:17,260
 and wonder why God would do that for them

638
00:28:17,260 --> 00:28:18,340
 but not do it for us.

639
00:28:18,340 --> 00:28:19,660
 And yet the truth of this story is saying,

640
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:22,340
 He's got plenty to give.

641
00:28:22,340 --> 00:28:26,220
 He literally, He says to Cain, He says,

642
00:28:26,220 --> 00:28:30,020
 "If you do well, will you not be accepted?"

643
00:28:30,020 --> 00:28:31,300
 You see, He's communicating,

644
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:34,100
 "Hey bro, I've got favor to spare.

645
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:37,680
 "I've got an inexhaustible well of blessing.

646
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,320
 "So why are you worried?

647
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,800
 "Why are you stressed?

648
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:42,160
 "Why are you resentful?

649
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,380
 "Why do you envy?

650
00:28:43,380 --> 00:28:45,780
 "I've got everything and more that you could want.

651
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,480
 "So hey, you didn't do it today.

652
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,700
 "That's okay.

653
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,180
 "Let's try again tomorrow.

654
00:28:50,180 --> 00:28:51,560
 "Let's try again the next day.

655
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:53,120
 "Like, let's not give up right now.

656
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,820
 "Like, let's just continue to go.

657
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:56,260
 "Let's keep on walking.

658
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:57,620
 "Let's keep on talking.

659
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:59,320
 "Let's keep on processing.

660
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:00,660
 "Let's not give up on the fact

661
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:03,820
 "that there is favor enough for you all."

662
00:29:03,820 --> 00:29:10,580
 God's position towards us, as is true for Cain,

663
00:29:10,580 --> 00:29:12,460
 it never changed.

664
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:13,940
 Like, we don't deserve it,

665
00:29:13,940 --> 00:29:17,020
 but a loving God is still beckoning an unlovely people

666
00:29:17,020 --> 00:29:18,500
 to repent and come home.

667
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,460
 We don't deserve it,

668
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:24,100
 but a forgiving God is still seeking an unforgivable people

669
00:29:24,100 --> 00:29:27,780
 because He can call them to forgiveness

670
00:29:27,780 --> 00:29:29,660
 and bring them into right relationship.

671
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:30,700
 We don't deserve it,

672
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:32,020
 but Christ, the favorable,

673
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:33,920
 has laid down His life for the unfavorable

674
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:36,260
 that we might receive blessing from God again.

675
00:29:36,260 --> 00:29:40,140
 You see, God's position towards us has not changed.

676
00:29:40,140 --> 00:29:41,580
 Let me just ask you then.

677
00:29:41,580 --> 00:29:46,980
 Has yours?

678
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:51,700
 If His position hasn't changed,

679
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:53,660
 if He looks at you and He loves you and He accepts you

680
00:29:53,660 --> 00:29:55,500
 and He values you and He wants you,

681
00:29:55,500 --> 00:30:00,500
 what's your position have to say in response?

682
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:04,380
 It's crazy.

683
00:30:04,380 --> 00:30:06,820
 We see in the story that though God's position

684
00:30:06,820 --> 00:30:09,100
 towards Cain has not changed,

685
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:12,580
 Cain's position towards God has changed.

686
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:13,940
 That's what we pick up as we keep reading.

687
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:14,940
 Look at verse eight.

688
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:16,300
 "Cain spoke to Abel, his brother,

689
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:17,160
 "and when they were in the field,

690
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:20,160
 "Cain rose up against his brother Abel and he killed him.

691
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:21,160
 "Then the Lord said to Cain,

692
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,160
 "Where is Abel your brother?"

693
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,600
 That interesting.

694
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:28,360
 It's the same question he asked Eve in the last chapter.

695
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:32,140
 He says, "What have you done?"

696
00:30:32,140 --> 00:30:36,460
 The same question he asked Eve in the last chapter.

697
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:37,580
 "The voice of your brother's blood

698
00:30:37,580 --> 00:30:39,300
 "is crying to me from the ground,

699
00:30:39,300 --> 00:30:40,820
 "and now you're cursed from the ground,

700
00:30:40,820 --> 00:30:42,180
 "which has opened its mouth to receive

701
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,860
 "your brother's blood from your hand.

702
00:30:43,860 --> 00:30:45,180
 "When you work the ground,

703
00:30:45,180 --> 00:30:47,560
 "it'll no longer yield to you its strength.

704
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:49,920
 "You shall be a fugitive, a wanderer on the earth.

705
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,480
 "And so Cain said to the Lord,

706
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:54,020
 "My punishment, it's greater than I can bear.

707
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:56,500
 "Behold, you've driven me today away from the ground,

708
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:58,020
 "and from your face I shall be hidden.

709
00:30:58,020 --> 00:31:00,300
 "I'll be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth.

710
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:02,460
 "Whoever finds me, they're gonna kill me."

711
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:08,800
 This story, it's so tragic for me,

712
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,020
 because as I read it,

713
00:31:11,020 --> 00:31:16,540
 I see something that I think we often miss.

714
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:19,700
 You see, if we were to ask people,

715
00:31:19,700 --> 00:31:20,660
 just the general public,

716
00:31:20,660 --> 00:31:23,100
 hey, what's the story of Cain and Abel about?

717
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:25,260
 Most people would look at us and they would just say,

718
00:31:25,260 --> 00:31:26,700
 "Murder, it's about murder.

719
00:31:26,700 --> 00:31:28,020
 "One guy killed his brother."

720
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:29,060
 And they wouldn't be wrong,

721
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:31,860
 because this is the first recorded murder in human history.

722
00:31:31,860 --> 00:31:34,140
 We see Cain rise up and strike his brother down.

723
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:35,540
 And yet what's fascinating about it

724
00:31:35,540 --> 00:31:37,540
 is it takes all of one sentence

725
00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:41,660
 to explain that specific detail.

726
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:43,820
 But there are 20 sentences here

727
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:47,540
 over-viewing this account of Cain's life,

728
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:49,300
 but one sentence given to murder.

729
00:31:49,300 --> 00:31:51,460
 I'm not much of a true crime podcast guy,

730
00:31:51,460 --> 00:31:54,180
 but that doesn't make for a really compelling arc.

731
00:31:54,180 --> 00:31:57,100
 Like we don't see him concoct some maniacal plan.

732
00:31:57,100 --> 00:31:59,740
 We don't see him brandish some sort of murder weapon.

733
00:31:59,740 --> 00:32:02,460
 He doesn't hide a body or flee the scene.

734
00:32:02,460 --> 00:32:04,660
 He just looks at his brother and is like,

735
00:32:04,660 --> 00:32:06,860
 "Hey man, you wanna go for a walk?"

736
00:32:06,860 --> 00:32:07,700
 Bam, like it's over.

737
00:32:07,700 --> 00:32:09,380
 You know, like that's all it takes

738
00:32:09,380 --> 00:32:10,740
 for the murder to take place.

739
00:32:10,740 --> 00:32:12,900
 And yet it begs the question for us then,

740
00:32:12,900 --> 00:32:15,860
 if that's true, what is this about?

741
00:32:15,860 --> 00:32:21,140
 I think it's about rivalry.

742
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:24,300
 I think this story is about rivalry.

743
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:28,380
 Two people competing in pursuit of the same goal.

744
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:31,020
 And you wanna know why I think that's so very tragic?

745
00:32:31,020 --> 00:32:36,620
 Because that which Cain wanted for,

746
00:32:36,620 --> 00:32:38,180
 the smile of God,

747
00:32:38,180 --> 00:32:42,980
 was not something he could earn.

748
00:32:42,980 --> 00:32:45,060
 'Cause you can't earn what you already have.

749
00:32:45,060 --> 00:32:48,540
 But it is something you can lose.

750
00:32:48,540 --> 00:32:50,660
 And he does.

751
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:52,340
 And we did.

752
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:56,620
 All of us, like sheep have gone astray.

753
00:32:56,620 --> 00:32:59,940
 Each of us, by way of our sin, are subject to death.

754
00:32:59,940 --> 00:33:02,500
 We have committed a criminal offense of our own.

755
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:05,220
 Not murder like this, but we have committed

756
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:07,900
 that crime of sinning against a holy God.

757
00:33:07,900 --> 00:33:10,620
 And therefore his right response to us

758
00:33:10,620 --> 00:33:16,020
 is not unfairness, but fairness.

759
00:33:16,020 --> 00:33:20,020
 Because you may not think that God always gives you

760
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:21,860
 what you deserve, but third point,

761
00:33:21,860 --> 00:33:24,900
 God always gives sin what it deserves.

762
00:33:24,900 --> 00:33:28,620
 God always gives sin what it deserves.

763
00:33:28,620 --> 00:33:31,300
 There's so many ironies in this story.

764
00:33:31,300 --> 00:33:33,580
 I had to keep myself from writing.

765
00:33:33,580 --> 00:33:34,780
 Isn't it ironic?

766
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:35,620
 Isn't it ironic?

767
00:33:35,620 --> 00:33:37,060
 Because they're just all over the place, man.

768
00:33:37,060 --> 00:33:39,860
 Like this whole story is one giant irony.

769
00:33:39,860 --> 00:33:41,700
 But I think maybe the biggest one

770
00:33:41,700 --> 00:33:44,060
 is that Cain's problem with God's unfairness

771
00:33:44,060 --> 00:33:45,860
 in blessing Abel's actions

772
00:33:47,460 --> 00:33:51,140
 is actually overcome by God's fairness

773
00:33:51,140 --> 00:33:53,300
 in condemning his own.

774
00:33:53,300 --> 00:33:54,820
 Like, here's the thing.

775
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:58,220
 Despite what we might feel about God being unfair

776
00:33:58,220 --> 00:34:01,300
 or him being unjust or him being prejudiced against us,

777
00:34:01,300 --> 00:34:04,620
 what we must know that the scriptures declare loud and clear

778
00:34:04,620 --> 00:34:07,820
 is God is fair.

779
00:34:07,820 --> 00:34:09,540
 He is fair.

780
00:34:09,540 --> 00:34:10,380
 He is fair.

781
00:34:10,380 --> 00:34:14,380
 He will deal with all sin, whether it is now

782
00:34:14,380 --> 00:34:16,120
 or it is later.

783
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:19,380
 We know he is not patient as some count patience,

784
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:21,860
 but he is desiring that all would come

785
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:23,780
 to the knowledge of his repentance.

786
00:34:23,780 --> 00:34:26,380
 That's what 2 Peter 3 tells us.

787
00:34:26,380 --> 00:34:29,260
 We know he's holy, he's righteous, he's just.

788
00:34:29,260 --> 00:34:30,280
 And because that is true,

789
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,940
 he will not overlook a single offense.

790
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:35,420
